<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00120</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROHIBITING HARASSMENT AND INVASION OF PRIVACY FOR COMMERCIAL PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to penalize any person who shall commit harassment against any person for commercial purposes by: a.) Reclusion temporal and a fine of Fifty Thousand Pesos, if death is caused by such harassment; b.) Prison mayor and a fine of Twenty Thousand Pesos, if seriously bodily injury is proximately caused by such harassment; and c.) Arresto mayor and a fine of One Thousand Pesos, if neither death nor serious bodily injury is proximately caused by such harassment.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>MACAPAGAL ARROYO, JUAN MIGUEL</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Vergara (000 2019-08-14)</td><td>2. Sy-Alvarado (000 2019-09-20)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON JUSTICE ON 2019-07-23</td></tr></table>